# Boring, standard LLVM-based C style, adapted to this codebase.
#
# Deviations from stock LLVM, each justified by the existing code or by the
# byte-exact reverse-engineering goal:
#   IndentWidth 4        - the tree is overwhelmingly 4-space indented.
#   ColumnLimit 0        - lots of intentionally long lines, including
#                          column-aligned BP-offset/stack-layout comments that
#                          document the MSC 5.1 hash allocation; reflowing them
#                          would destroy load-bearing documentation.
#   SortIncludes false   - include grouping/order is deliberate; reordering is
#                          the most likely way to break this finicky build.
#   Short if/loops kept  - the code pervasively uses `if (cond) return x;`.
Language: Cpp
BasedOnStyle: LLVM
LineEnding: LF
IndentWidth: 4
ColumnLimit: 0
SortIncludes: false
AllowShortIfStatementsOnASingleLine: WithoutElse
AllowShortLoopsOnASingleLine: true
AllowShortBlocksOnASingleLine: Empty
